.TH "emac_dev_stop" 9 "emac_dev_stop" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
emac_dev_stop \- EMAC device stop
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" emac_dev_stop
.BI "(struct net_device *ndev "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ndev" 12
The DaVinci EMAC network adapter
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Called when system wants to stop or down the interface. We stop the network
queue, disable interrupts and cleanup TX/RX channels.

We return the statistics in net_device_stats structure pulled from emac
